6:
Wow, that shopkeeper wasn't
kidding—this place is completely
packed!
9:
From what I've heard, people come
here to make their wishes for the
new year. Got anything in mind?
14:
I do, in fact! To become a famous
adventurer someday.
20:
It'll take more than a simple prayer
to make that happen.
24:
I-I know that! I'll be putting in my
own effort too!
27:
I mean, I've already grown so much
exploring the Kaleidoscope with you
guys—even the people in the guild
are starting to respect me!
32:
Your efforts have not gone
unnoticed, Rebecca. Just keep at it
at your own pace.
35: I believe in you too, Rebecca.
46:
I've been meaning to ask you, by the
way—what's in those boxes over
there? They look an awful lot like the
one you're holding.
49:
They're fortune boxes! The
shopkeeper told me all about them
when I bought my outfit.
51:
Inside the boxes are numbers you
can draw to see your fortune for the
new year, and... um...
55:
More importantly, why is everyone
staring at me?!
63: I KNEW this skirt was way too short!
69:
Now that I get a good look at the
others, I suppose yours does stand
out a bit...
74:
Waaaaugh! Okay, I'm gonna
change for real this time!
84:
But everyone's staring! Why else
would they look at me?!
87:
It really IS you! You're the Shiruko
Shogun!
92:
Shiruko what now?
Wait, why do you know about that?
95:
I thought your face looked familiar!
Your shiruko stuffing prowess has
become the talk of all of Yamato!
97:
Good luck in all your future
endeavors, Lady Shogun!
99:
Three cheers for the Shiruko Shogun!
Hip hip, hooray! Hip hip, hooray! Hip
hip, hooray!!!
104:
Nooo! How far has that stupid
nickname spread?!
108:
Would ya look at that. You're already
famous.
113:
I didn't want to be famous—I mean,
not like this!
134:
We've gotta stop them before
somebody gets hurt!
140: We can't let them get past us!
151:
Uh-oh... What am I supposed to do
now?
155:
Grr... Why won't you guys listen to
me at a time like this?!
174:
Th-thanks, but it was mostly the
shadows that did the heavy lifting.
179: Thanks to you, nobody was hurt.
181:
We are forever indebted to you, Miss
Shogun—no, Miss DAIMYO!
189:
Ah, yes. A perfectly fitting title for
someone so utterly distinguished
such as yourself!
191:
Praise be to her glutinousness, the
honorable Shiruko Daimyo, Rebecca
the Great!
195:
Can someone PLEASE tell me what's
going on here?!
200:
Way to move up the ranks, Rebecca.
I'm impressed.
204:
I... Huh?! This isn't what I meant when
I said I wanted to become famous!
207:
I really have to be careful what I
wish for!
